          concept: 'User research in the curriculum is not a phase that ends before development begins. It is described as a constant state of awareness -- an attitude of seeking to understand the world as it is before proposing solutions to it. The fundamental distinction: observations are what you see. Insights are the why behind the behaviour. Observing that an analyst takes 70 hours to write a report is an observation. The insight might be that they are afraid AI will displace them -- and the elaborate manual process is a way of proving their irreplaceability. A product that optimises the 70-hour process misses the real problem entirely. CORE CONCEPTS',
