          whyInPath: 'Stakeholder Management is one of your key growth areas -- building real competency here will be your biggest unlock as a PM candidate.',
          videoDuration: '18 min',
          textDuration: '12 min',
          videoId: 'dQw4w9WgXcQ',
          concept: 'PMs have enormous responsibility and almost no direct authority. You cannot order the engineering team to build something. You cannot force the design team to change direction. You cannot tell the CEO that their favourite feature is not getting built. Everything a PM accomplishes is done through influence, alignment, and trust -- not authority. Stakeholder management is the practice of building those things deliberately. The most common failure: PMs who walk into stakeholder conversations with the answer already decided, and use the conversation to sell rather than to listen. People can feel when they are being sold to rather than consulted. ',
