          textDuration: '12 min',
          videoId: 'dQw4w9WgXcQ',
          concept: 'In product management, almost everything consequential happens through documents -- strategy memos, product requirement docs, decision write-ups, post-mortems, launch briefs. Your documents are your most visible work. They are what people share when you are not in the room. A well-written document travels further than you do. A document full of vague ideas and unexplained decisions makes people feel uncertain about your judgment -- even if your instincts are excellent. The most important shift: think of a document not as a final answer but as a thinking tool. You do not write a document because you have figured everything out. You write a doc',
